.SH SHMultiply
Multiply two functions and determine the spherical harmonic coefficients
of the resulting function.
.SH Usage
call SHMultiply (\f[CR]cilmout\f[R], \f[CR]cilm1\f[R], \f[CR]lmax1\f[R],
\f[CR]cilm2\f[R], \f[CR]lmax2\f[R], \f[CR]precomp\f[R], \f[CR]norm\f[R],
\f[CR]csphase\f[R], \f[CR]exitstatus\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]cilmout\f[R] : output, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmax1\f[R]+\f[CR]lmax2\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmax1\f[R]+\f[CR]lmax2\f[R]+1)
The real spherical harmonic coefficients corresponding to the
multiplication of \f[CR]cilm1\f[R] and \f[CR]cilm2\f[R] in the space
domain.
.TP
\f[CR]cilm1\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmax1\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmax1\f[R]+1)
The spherical harmonic coefficients of the first function.
.TP
\f[CR]lmax1\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The maximum spherical harmonic degree used in evaluting
\f[CR]cilm1\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]cilm2\f[R] : input, real(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmax2\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmax2\f[R]+1)
The spherical harmonic coefficients of the second function.
.TP
\f[CR]lmax2\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The maximum spherical harmonic degree used in evaluting
\f[CR]cilm2\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]precomp\f[R] : input, optional, integer(int32), default = 0
If 1, the array of Legendre functions \f[CR]plx\f[R] will be precomputed
on the Gauss\-Legendre quadrature nodes.
.TP
\f[CR]norm\f[R] : input, optional, integer(int32), default = 1
1 (default) = Geodesy 4\-pi normalized harmonics; 2 = Schmidt
semi\-normalized harmonics; 3 = unnormalized harmonics; 4 = orthonormal
harmonics.
.TP
\f[CR]csphase\f[R] : input, optional, integer(int32), default = 1
1 (default) = do not apply the Condon\-Shortley phase factor to the
associated Legendre functions; \-1 = append the Condon\-Shortley phase
