.SH Description
\f[CR]SHMultiply\f[R] will take two sets of spherical harmonic
coefficients, multiply the functions in the space domain, and expand the
resulting field in spherical harmonics using \f[CR]SHExpandGLQ\f[R].
The spherical harmonic bandwidth of the resulting field is
\f[CR]lmax1+lmax2\f[R], where \f[CR]lmax1\f[R] and \f[CR]lmax2\f[R] are
the bandwidths of the input fields.
If the optional parameter \f[CR]precomp\f[R] is set, then the array of
Legendre functions \f[CR]plx\f[R] will be precomputed on the
Gauss\-Legendre quadrature nodes.
.PP
The employed spherical harmonic normalization and Condon\-Shortley phase
convention can be set by the optional arguments \f[CR]norm\f[R] and
\f[CR]csphase\f[R]; if not set, the default is to use geodesy 4\-pi
normalized harmonics that exclude the Condon\-Shortley phase of
(\-1)\(ham.
